Be-Pass Cookie Policy
Effective Date: Feb 25, 2025

1. Introduction
This Cookie Policy explains how SMART WORKOUT APP LTD ("Be-Pass," "we," "us," or "our") uses cookies and similar tracking technologies when you visit our website (www.be-pass.com), use our mobile application, or engage with the services provided through them (collectively, the "Service").

By using the Service, you agree to the use of cookies as outlined in this policy. You may manage or withdraw your consent at any time (see Section 5: Managing Cookies).

2. What Are Cookies?
Cookies are small text files stored on your device (computer, tablet, or mobile) when you visit a website or use an application. Cookies help us improve functionality, analyze usage, personalize content, and enhance your user experience.

Cookies may be either:

Session cookies: Temporary and deleted when you close your browser.
Persistent cookies: Remain on your device until they expire or you delete them.
3. Types of Cookies We Use
3.1 Essential Cookies
These cookies are necessary for the operation of our Service. Without them, certain features (like account login and secure navigation) will not function properly.

Examples:

Authentication cookies
Security cookies
3.2 Performance and Analytics Cookies
These cookies collect information about how users interact with our Service, helping us understand usage patterns, measure performance, and improve functionality.

Tools used:

Google Analytics
Crashlytics
Data collected may include:

Pages visited
Click interactions
Device information
3.3 Functional Cookies
These cookies allow the Service to remember choices you make (such as language preferences or location) to provide enhanced, personalized features.

3.4 Advertising and Marketing Cookies
These cookies are used to deliver relevant advertisements and track the effectiveness of marketing campaigns.

We may use:

Google Advertising ID (AAID)
Apple Identifier for Advertising (IDFA)
3.5 Third-Party Cookies
Third-party services integrated into our Service may place cookies on your device. We do not control these cookies and recommend reviewing their privacy policies.

Examples of third-party services:

Google Ads
Facebook Pixel
LinkedIn Analytics
4. Why We Use Cookies
We use cookies to:
Provide and maintain the Service
Enable secure sign-ins and account management
Analyze usage to improve performance
Personalize content and recommendations
Deliver targeted advertising and measure its effectiveness

5. Managing Cookies
You can control and manage cookies in several ways:

5.1 Browser Settings
Most browsers allow you to:

View cookies
Delete cookies
Block cookies
Note: Blocking cookies may affect the functionality of the Service.

5.2 Mobile Device Settings
iOS: Settings → Privacy → Tracking
Android: Settings → Privacy → Ads
5.3 Opt-Out Options
Google Analytics: Opt-Out Browser Add-on
Network Advertising Initiative: NAI Opt-Out Page
6. Updates to This Cookie Policy
We may update this Cookie Policy from time to time. Significant changes will be notified via the Service or by email. The date of the latest revision will always appear at the top of this document.

7. Contact Us
For any questions regarding this Cookie Policy, contact us at:

SMART WORKOUT APP LTD
Email: bepassfeedback@gmail.com
